8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 768, L.D. 1961, “An Act to Clarify the
10 Laws Relating to the Licensure of Certain Facilities by the Department of Health and
11 Human Services”
12 Amend the bill in Part C by inserting after section 1 the following:
13 'Sec. C-2. 22 MRSA §1812-G, sub-§3-B, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 241, §9, is
14 amended to read:
15 3-B. Petition for removal of a substantiated finding of neglect or
16 misappropriation of property. No sooner than 12 months after the date a substantiated
17 finding of neglect or misappropriation of property is placed on the registry, a direct care
18 worker may petition the department to remove the notation from the registry if the
19 substantiated complaint finding is a one-time occurrence and there is no pattern of neglect
20 or misappropriation of property.'
21 Amend the bill in Part C in section 4 in subsection 6 in the 2nd line (page 6, line 14 in
22 L.D.) by striking out the following: "complaint" and inserting the following: 'finding'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment makes a correction to the bill that a substantiated finding, rather than
2277 a substantiated complaint, is a disqualifying offense prohibiting employment in the laws
2288 governing the Maine Registry of Certified Nursing Assistants and Direct Care Workers.
2299 The amendment also corrects a reference to a substantiated complaint in the provision
3300 governing a petition to remove the notation of a substantiated finding from the registry.
3311 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
